cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.CY

This paper deals with privacy-preserving measurement of the Tor anonymity network, which involves aspects of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The use of differential privacy and secure aggregation techniques also involves aspects of data structures (cs.DS) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the study of Tor usage behavior and onion services involves aspects of cybersecurity (cs.CY).
